e-Rupee (Digital Rupee)

The e-Rupee is India’s Central Bank Digital Currency (CBDC) issued by the Reserve Bank of India (RBI). 
It is a digital form of physical cash and has the same value as paper currency.

Launch in India
Issued by: Reserve Bank of India (RBI)
Wholesale e-Rupee (e₹-W): Launched in November 2022
Retail e-Rupee (e₹-R): Launched in December 2022

Key Features of e-Rupee
Legal tender in digital form
Safe and stable, backed by RBI
Non-interest bearing
Convertible to cash and bank deposits
Works through digital wallets

How e-Rupee Works
Users store e-Rupee in digital wallets provided by banks
Can be used for:
Person-to-Person (P2P) payments
Person-to-Merchant (P2M) payments
Banks act as intermediaries between RBI and users

Types of e-Rupee
e₹-W (Wholesale): Used by banks for interbank transactions
e₹-R (Retail): Used by the public for daily transactions



Why e-Rupee Was Introduced
Promote digital payments
Reduce dependence on cash
Improve financial inclusion
Make payment systems faster and cheaper

e-Rupee vs Cryptocurrency
e-Rupee
Cryptocurrency
Issued by RBI
No central authority
Stable value
Highly volatile
Legal tender
Not legal tender
Regulated
Mostly unregulated


Conclusion
The e-Rupee is a secure and modern form of money that combines the trust of cash with the convenience of digital payments, helping India move toward a digital economy.

